The last thing to verify is that the application is actually reachable through the NodePort:

kubectl get nodes -o wide

Then test it (replace <NODE-IP> with the node's internal IP if needed):

curl http://<NODE-IP>:32345

or, since this is a single-node K3s cluster running on jump-host, you can often test locally:

curl http://localhost:32345

or

curl http://127.0.0.1:32345

If the lab still reports failure despite the pod and service looking correct, run:

kubectl get deployment python-deployment-devops -o yaml | grep image

The expected image should be:

poroko/flask-demo-app

If that's what you have, your configuration matches the task requirements and the application should be accessible on NodePort 32345.
